Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop the @cauliflower florets{300} into a #mixing bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir in the @mayonnaise{2}. Make sure the florets are well coated. In another small #bowl{}, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} with half the @Central American style spice mix{1}. Season the crumbs with salt and stir in a glug of @oil{}. Tip the crumbs onto the florets and toss to coat evenly.

Carefully transfer the florets to a lined #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}. Discard any crumbs that are left in the bowl.

Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Transfer a third to a bowl and crush with a #fork{} (we will use these later to thicken the bean stew). Trim the @courgette{1}, quarter lengthways, then chop widthways into small chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(deseeded and finely chopped) lengthways, deseed and finely chop. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(chopped, stalks and all). Slice the @halloumi{250%g} into 3 slices per person.

Heat a splash of oil in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add the courgette and cook, stirring for ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and remaining spice mix, cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped) and @water{75%ml}. Bring to a simmer, then leave to bubble away for ~{5%minutes}. After 5 mins, add the whole and crushed beans to the stew. Cook until the stew is nice and thick, ~{5-6%minutes} more.

Do any washing up now whilst everything is cooking. Once the cauliflower has 6 mins left to cook, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, lay in the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. When the cauliflower is ready, remove from the oven. Stir half the coriander into the stew, then remove from the heat. Season the stew with salt and as much red chilli as you like!

Spoon the spicy bean stew into #bowls{} and add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}. Carefully arrange the cauliflower nuggets and halloumi on top and finish with a sprinkling of remaining coriander. Enjoy!

> If you've added halloumi to your meal, slice the halloumi into 3 slices per person at the end of the step where you add the halloumi. Then follow the rest of the recipe.

> If you've added halloumi to your meal. Once the cauliflower has 6 mins left to cook, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium high heat. Once hot, lay in the halloumi and fry until golden, 2-3 mins each side. Follow the rest of the recipe as instructed.

> If you've added halloumi to your meal, serve on top of the stew with the cauliflower.